<item>
  <title>linear independence</title>
  <link>https://cryscham123.github.io/posts/02_areas/선형대수/notes/06.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p><img src="https://cryscham123.github.io/img/human-thumb.jpg" class="post-thumbnail img-fluid"></p>
<section id="linear-independence" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="linear-independence">Linear independence</h2>
<section id="definition" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="definition">Definition</h3>
<ul>
<li>Dependence: one of the vectors in the set can be written as a linear combination of the others.</li>
<li>Independence: ⫬ dependence</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="theorem" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="theorem">Theorem</h3>
<p>S = <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%7Bv_1,%20v_2,%20...,%20v_n%7D"></p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?S"> is linearly dependent ⟺ ∃(<img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c_i"> is not 0) <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c_1v_1%20+%20c_2v_2%20+%20...%20+%20c_nv_n%20=%200"> is <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c_1%20=%20c_2%20=%20...%20=%20c_n%20=%200">.</p>
<ul>
<li>if <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c_1%20=%20c_2%20=%20...%20=%20c_n%20=%200">, then <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?S"> is linearly independent.</li>
</ul>


</section>
</section>

